                            <comment id="14511261" author="githubbot" created="Fri, 24 Apr 2015 15:53:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;GitHub user mreve opened a pull request:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/thrift/pull/461&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/thrift/pull/461&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    Support negative hex literals in IDL&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    As it is now, the parser doesn&apos;t allow hex constant values to be negative (it throws a &apos;bad syntax&apos; error).&lt;br/&gt;
    The change updates the regex and the code that parses the hex value from the string read from the IDL file to support negative values.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    Jira issue: &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-233&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-233&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

