&lt;p&gt;    This closes #461&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;commit 5c14cea3d612d026279b354556472c22647261b9&lt;br/&gt;
Author: mreve &amp;lt;aadymek@gmail.com&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Date:   2015-04-19T11:16:45Z&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    Update hexconstant regex in thriftl.ll&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    As it is now, the parser doesn&apos;t allow hex constant values to be negative (it throws a &apos;bad syntax&apos; error).&lt;br/&gt;
    The change updates the regex and the part that parses the hex value from the string read from the IDL file to support negative values.&lt;/p&gt;

